children.subject:
If you are L & S, i say Data 100 is easier than 16b so I would take it with 70 to have more time allocated to 70.
Which leaves you with 16b and 61c which is probably gonna be a sucky semester but everyone has to go through a tough semester once in a while. 

If you are not L & S, just don’t take 70 and 61c together. Personally, I did 70 and 16b Fall 2021 and I found it to be somewhat chill. Tip: read the notes for both classes and go to discussion, lecture sucks lol

I think having a taking one pset class (70, 16b) and coding class (100, 61c) together is a good balance. Check out the professors for the next year when they come out and see which combo you would prefer.
I personally think 61C is probably by far the hardest workload wise. If declaration & such is not an issue I would recommend 16B & 70 in one semester and then data100 & 61C the next

thank you in advance
